OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FRegion sees surge in       
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fout-of-control dog         
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fincidents                  
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The number of incidents involving      
OL,6, out-of-control dogs has risen,         
OL,7, according to figures from Avon &       
OL,8, Somerset Police.                       
OL,10,FOffences in the force area rose from   
OL,11,F556 in 2020 to 641 in 2022.            
OL,13,FBristol-based dog trainer Roz Pooley,  
OL,14,Fwho runs the Mutty Professor training  
OL,15,Fschool, said there was a surge in dog  
OL,16,Fownership during lockdown.             
OL,18,FShe said: "Some breeders were getting  
OL,19,Flitters out quickly to make money. I've
OL,20,Fcome across a lot of cases where dogs  
OL,21,Fweren't socialised during lockdown."   
